<headline>Heat Advisory issued July 17 at 2:09AM CDT until July 18 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...HEAT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 9 PM CDT THIS
EVENING...
...HEAT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM TO 9 PM CDT TUESDAY...
* WHAT...For the first Heat Advisory, temperatures up to 105
expected. For the second Heat Advisory, temperatures up to 108
expected.
* WHERE...Palo Duro Canyon State Park.
* WHEN...For the first Heat Advisory, from 1 PM this afternoon to 9
PM CDT this evening. For the second Heat Advisory, from 1 PM to 9
PM CDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.</description>
<instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, keep physical activity limited to the early
morning hours, and wear light colored clothing.</instruction>
